      <odd id="aspace_126e686307c38999d3e769a11ea5d8c9">
         <head>General note</head>
         <p>Forms part of Yale Record Group 45 (YRG 45), Yale objects and memorabilia.</p>  
      </odd>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_016f7df1de5a1e83f445f258a9b20b0e">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The materials were donated by Richard Hamilton, 2001, and Ann B. Hamilton, 2011.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_551656f88e2dc375f0ab78bd19033daf">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_c8aa61579d36f7371937982dbb4dad87">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Harry T. Hamilton, Class of 1904, Yale College, Memorabilia (RU 897). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <arrangement id="aspace_db1436c304c30b82592a1cab4fcae3b3">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The memorabilia is arranged by accession.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_cf5dc30c9922ea2b0e0176ae239997b6">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The materials consist of a scrapbook, photographs, a calendar celebrating Yale's 1901 bicentennial, the Class of 1901's valedictory poem and oration, and other assorted printed materials documenting Harry T. Hamilton's (Yale 1904) life as a student at Yale. Included is a memoir by Henry Bancroft Twombly, a Yale football player, and an edition of Yale, A Record of the Dinner, February 16, 1889.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
